values: Step 1: Post this into your LJ publicly. Step 2: Others will reply anonymously about what they really think of you. Step 3: Cry, because this meme is so brutal, & it hurts. :P

1. Your state flag?: 2. The last thing you drank?: 3. Your favourite fruit?: 4. A picture you took this week, month, year, etc.?: 5. Favourite instrument(s)?: 6. Favourite breakfast food?: 7. What is your favourite movie?: 8. Most watched sport?: 9. Favourite topping on a pizza?: 10. Favourite vegetable(s)?: 11. Favourite websites?: 12. Where do you get your music?: 13. Your favourite colour?: 14. Way you express yourself?: 15. Your state bird?: 16. A dead person you like/admire?: 17. Your favourite musician?:

1. What did you do in 2008 that you’d never done before?
Went to university.

2. Did you keep your New Years’ resolutions, & will you make more for next year?
My resolution has been to lose weight for the past few years & this year I mostly certainly did not keep it! However, I will endeavour to keep it next year, I’m quite determined this time.

3. Did anyone close to you give birth?
Yes, Jemma!

4. Did anyone close to you die?
Not anyone really close but I know of some people that died.

5. What countries did you visit?
Only places in the UK.

6. What would you like to have in 2009 that you lacked in 2008?
Motivation for a healthier lifestyle.

7. What date from 2008 will remain etched upon your memory, & why?
21st September, moving down day for Freshers at university & the start of my new life!

8. What was your biggest achievement of the year?
I’ve been getting 2.1s so far at university so that’s pretty cool, but also feeling like I’ve done some good for the kids when I worked at the Lea.

9. What was your biggest failure?
Putting on loads of weight, sigh.

10. Did you suffer illness or injury?
The flu & some colds, a few cuts & bruises, nothing major.

11. What was the best thing you bought?
XBox, some other things.

12. What was the worst thing you bought?
Well, we worked out how much money I’ve wasted on cigarettes over the years that I’d been smoking & it turned out to be thousands of pounds, so probably fags!

13. Number 13, anything unlucky happen this year?
I got clamped a few weeks ago. :\

14. Where did most of your money go?
Drink, food (at uni), fags, petrol.

15. What did you get really, really, really excited about?
Eddie Izzard, university, the Olympics in Beijing, the future.

16. What song will always remind you of 2008?
Guru Josh Project - Infinity 2008 & loads of other songs that are constantly played in halls.

Compared to this time last year, are you:
17. Thinner or fatter?
Fatter, dammit.

18. Richer or poorer?
Poorer - I’m a student these days, no full-time job!

19. What do you wish you’d done more of?
Eating healthily & exercising, sorting myself out so that I didn’t leave certain areas of my life in such a mess.

20. What do you wish you’d done less of?
Wishing bad things upon other people, hangovers, spending money on shit I don’t need.

21. How did you spend Christmas?
With Claire & my parents in the morning, then with Mum & Dad in the afternoon & for most of the rest of the day, finally at Daniel’s in the evening.

22. Did you fall in love in 2008?
Too late for that craziness.

23. What was your favourite TV programme?
Watching X Factor as a hall was great fun.

24. Do you hate anyone now that you didn't hate this time last year?
As I’m sure I’ve said a thousand times before, hate is a very strong word. I don’t really hate anyone as such, but there are definitely certain people that can go fuck themselves. :)

25. What was the best book you read?
Frankenstein has been pretty awesome to be honest - I read a lot of old Stephen King books that I hadn’t read before & also a new one: Duma Key.

26. What was your greatest musical discovery?
There have been many this year, especially when I came to university & going out clubbing, listening to the latest tunage... I realised that Iron Maiden aren’t so bad & The Script & Dispatch are pretty awesome too.

27. What did you want & get?
Uggs, XBox, money, the beginnings of a higher education.

28. What did you want & not get?
A dog!

29. What was your favourite film of this year?
The Dark Knight, Mamma Mia! & Hancock.

30. What did you do on your birthday, & how old were you?
21 & I got drunk in Reading.

31. What one thing would have made your year immeasurably more satisfying?
Having people get what’s coming to them... & maybe also not being such a stupid bitch at times.

32. How would you describe your personal fashion concept in 2008?
Mine, as always.

33. What kept you sane?
Thoughts of my so-called ten-year life plan. It’s gonna be great.

34. Which celebrity/public figure did you fancy the most?
I guess I haven’t really thought about it too much but there are definitely some pretty people out there nowadays.

35. What political issue stirred you the most?
Obama & the US presidential race. So exciting!

36. Who did you miss?
I don’t really know, myself sometimes (haha, emo); when I went to uni I missed my friends, my parents, Eddie.

37. Who was the best new person you met?
All the lovely uni people!

38. Tell us a valuable life lesson you learned in 2008:
You can shine no matter what you’re made of & Just because I love you, doesn’t mean that I can’t hate you.

39. Quote a song lyric that sums up your year:
“Every new beginning comes from some other beginning’s end.” - Semisonic

The Ultimate 2007 Survey

YOU
Did your appearance change this year?:: I took out all but 6 piercings, got 3 new tattoos & changed my hair a lot.
Did you grow emotionally?:: I'd like to think so.
Did you improve at anything?:: Being happier.
Did you discover any new talents?:: Putting a brave face on things.
Did you dye your hair?:: Every 5 weeks.
Did you get any really cool presents?:: A car, a new TV, money, jewellery...
Did you get in trouble for anything?:: Probably. :\
Did you get any awards?:: I don't reckon so.
What's something that you're proud of?:: Helping the kids at school & living my life a little more legally.
Did you do anything that you regret?:: I don't regret.
What did you do on your last birthday?:: Got pissed at Q Bar.
Did anything weird happen to you?:: Not really?
Did you stay up all night?:: A few times.
Did you throw any parties?: No but I went to a few.
Did you get drunk?:: A lot.
Did you get high?:: Once or twice - oops!
Did you go on any vacations?:: I went out of the country twice (Gran Canaria & Tenerife) & had long weekends in Yorkshire & Ipswich.
Did you do well in school?:: I did my Law A-level but didn't do all that well.
Did you have fun this year?:: Yes. :)

FRIENDS
Did you make any new friends this year?:: Lots.
Did you lose any friends?:: Yes, about the same amount that I made!
Did you have any wild times with your friends?:: New Year's, various birthdays, Global Gathering, Reading Festival, nights out...
Who are your best friends?:: I don't like to pick favourites.
Did you fight a lot with friends?:: It happens.
What's a memorable time you had with friends?:: New Year's was good.
Did any of your friends become MORE than friends?:: Not this year.
Did you run up your cell phone bill talking to friends?:: A couple of times.
Which friend did you hang with the most?:: People from Reading or the Pond House.

LOVE
Did you fall in love this year?:: Heh.
Did you have a steady boyfriend/girlfriend?:: Yes.
How many people did you date this year?:: One.
Were you romantically happy this year?:: Um... mostly.
Did you kiss anyone this year?:: Of course.
Were you happy being single this year?:: I wasn't single.
Did you have a summer fling?:: I had a year-long fling, it's still going on!
Did anyone ask you out but you said no?:: Yes.
Do you have a boyfriend/girlfriend right now?:: Yep.
Is one of your New Year resolutions to get one?:: No.
Did you get your heart broken this year?:: If my heart was broken I'd be dead. :)

EXPERIENCES
Name one memorable experience:: Both my holidays were awesome - I'd not been away for years!
Name one inside joke from 2007:: "Where is her vagina?!?!?!" Reading Festival... haha.
What's one place you wanted to go this year?:: I quite fancied Glastonbury Festival but I'm glad I didn't go in the end due to all the mud!
Did you do anything this year that you never thought you would do?:: Global Gathering Festival.
What's one thing you're really glad you did?:: Got this job at the school & applied for university.
What's one thing you really regret?:: Again, I don't regret.
Did you get arrested in 2007?:: No.
Did you get grounded?:: Don't be silly!
Did you get really sick?:: Having two jobs made me sick - never again!
Did you meet someone that changed your life?:: My life changed a lot but not necessarily due to anyone I met.
Did you go to any concerts?:: Yes - the Police, Rihanna & three festivals (Download, Global & Reading).
Did you meet anyone famous?:: Not really, only people I knew before.
Did you dance in the rain?:: Yes.
Did you skip school?:: No.
What was your worst experience of 2007?:: All the mud at Global, leaving Whiteknights IBC.
What was your best experience?:: Seeing my family from Yorkshire again.

LAST THOUGHTS
What was your best memory of 2007?:: Seeing old friends.
What was your worst memory of 2007?:: Worrying about a couple of close friends.
Did you keep your New Year's resolution from last year?:: Yes, bar a couple of slip ups.
What is your resolution for this year?:: Keep fit, lose weight & be healthy!
Do you think it will come true?:: Maybe, if I stick at it.
If you could have 3 wishes for 2008, what would they be?:: Understanding, love & happiness.
Was 2007 better than 2006?:: Yes.
Do you think 2008 will be a better year than 2007?:: It should be - although there are some big changes afoot (university)!
